# SDR Screener — Backend

No separate Express server. Backend = **Next.js Route Handlers** + **Supabase** + **n8n** (external workflow).

## API routes (`app/api/`)

| Route | Responsibility |
|-------|----------------|
| `GET /api/job-descriptions` | List current user's saved JDs |
| `POST /api/job-descriptions` | Create JD (`title`, `body`) |
| `PATCH /api/job-descriptions/[id]` | Update JD (owner only) |
| `DELETE /api/job-descriptions/[id]` | Delete JD (owner only; reject or soft-delete if candidates reference it) |
| `POST /api/upload/presign` | Return Supabase Storage signed upload URL (resume PDF, video mp4/webm) |
| `POST /api/screen` | Validate `job_description_id`, load `body` as `jd_text`, insert `candidates` row, fire n8n webhook |
| `GET /api/auth/callback` | Supabase auth code exchange |

Webhook payload to n8n: `{ candidate_id, resume_path, video_path?, jd_text }` where `jd_text` is resolved from `job_descriptions.body`. Use `N8N_SCREEN_WEBHOOK_URL` from env.

## Supabase (`supabase/`)

- **`job_descriptions`**: `id`, `user_id`, `title`, `body`, `created_at`, `updated_at`. RLS: owner-only CRUD.
- **`candidates`**: includes `job_description_id` (FK → `job_descriptions`); `status`: `processing` | `complete` | `failed`.
- **`screenings`**: `overall_score`, `summary`, `strengths`/`weaknesses` JSONB, `transcript`, `raw` jsonb.
- Enable **RLS** on all tables: users see only their own rows (`user_id` on `job_descriptions` and `candidates`).
- Storage buckets: `resumes`, `videos` — private, signed URLs for read/write.

Use `lib/supabase/server.ts` in routes; `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` only in server/n8n, never client.

## n8n (`n8n/`)

- **Source of truth** for scoring prompts: `n8n/prompts/` (system, user template, JSON schema).
- Production workflow: `n8n/workflows/v1-webhook-supabase.workflow.json`.
- Pipeline: download files → extract PDF text → Whisper if video → single OpenAI structured-output call → write `screenings` + set candidate `complete`.
- Do not duplicate rubric logic in Next.js — keep it in n8n prompts.

## AI scoring output shape

```json
{
  "overall_score": 0,
  "summary": "",
  "strengths": [{ "dimension": "", "score": 0, "evidence": "" }],
  "weaknesses": [{ "dimension": "", "score": 0, "evidence": "" }],
  "red_flags": []
}
```

Renormalize weights when video is missing (verbal_delivery, objection_handling → null).

## Env vars

See `.env.local.example`. Never commit secrets.

## Avoid

- Rubric tables or editable scoring weights in the app — rubric stays in n8n prompts only.
- Passing only `job_description_id` to n8n without resolving `jd_text` server-side first.
- Org/team/multi-tenant tables unless explicitly requested.
- Blocking on n8n in the API route — trigger webhook and return; n8n writes async.
- Streaming large files through Next.js or n8n webhook body.
